<br>
&quot;I suppose this puts an end to the whole, if walls could talk theory. maybe they just talk to the people they like,&quot; She stated, trying to be more cheerful. she fought back the need to cry.<br>
<br>
it was so frustrating, not being up there, not fighting. she felt weak, and helpless, at the mercy of the house. <br>
<br>
she felt like she did after her mother was murdered.<br>
<br>
her throat felt like it was constricting, and she couldn't cry infront of amanda. she forced the tears down, but with a fierce growl.<br>
<br>
&quot;Swven!&quot; She growled. &quot;You don't understand...&quot; She told him. his hand pressed reassuringly upon hers, and she ceased her frustrated pacing.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're still holding my hand...&quot; She told him, with a slight note of disbelief running in her voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm being stupid. I'm sure your boy can take them better than I can anyway.&quot; She told him, smiling into the dark. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alphakago>Alpha Kago</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(2/13/03 7:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm185.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/comics/lucifer.com/alpha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: your still holding my hand...</span><hr size=1> swven made no expression as usual to the words being spoken to him as the walls stood quiet and cold, swven stepped on something and it crushed underneath his foot. <br>
