Mahrain followed Swven to Amanda's crumpled form. another tear slid down her cheek. she bent down, her long auburn hair tumbling over her shoulders asshe reached out her hand.<br>
<br>
&quot;I had a friend. I only met her once, but she said something to me, something I'll never forget, and I hope you wont either. She said, humanity lies not in what we give up, but in what we hold onto. don't ever give up Amanda. Whoever this womans accomplices are, whatever she tries to do, we have friends also, and you are our friend, and so our friends are yours,&quot;<br>
<br>
She stood up, addressing both Amanda and Swven. &quot; I think that no matter how hard we try to run, we'll never be able to hide from scarlet, or her organization. I think people will have to fight. now, bear with me, but I have a bit of a tale to tell, and maybe when I'm through we'll all be in agreement.&quot;<br>
<br>
She paused, and gathered her breath. &quot;After my father was murdered, Felix hid me as a sister of his in his gajdi caravan. Gajdi is a sort of gypsy culture. I met his sister, Shalel, the girl who told me what I told you. she was a witch. in the Gajdi cuture, it is forbidden, though I know she is very powerful. <br>
<br>
after the caravan, Felix found me a job with a man I know only as 'The Boss' He's a recluse who lives under the city, a sorcerer of great power who strongly identifies with the side of right, and the righteous. for about two years now, he has been sending me on assignements, watching individuals whose purpose in his game has eluded me for sometime, but, I think there is a connection between Amanda's plight and my job. A few months back, I had been researching the mystery of the boss, and I noticed a pattern. a woman, named lillian. she seemed to have her fingers in everything that the boss did. I believe that the organization has an enemy, not just in me, but in the boss and all in his employ. if we created a coalition, a network, if you will, we could possibly put an end to this organization, and to scarlet.&quot;<br>
<br>
She pause, looking at their startled faces. &quot;I was thinking big...&quot; She mumbled. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alphakago>Alpha Kago</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(2/14/03 9:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm185.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/comics/lucifer.com/alpha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: don't give up hope</span><hr size=1> swven smiled somewhat dark and mysteriously as the count appeared behind him. &quot;Let's ask lillian shant we?&quot; he went back to his old tongue and walked out towards the pond and the count eyed him. 'Don't fall this time' the count said. <br>
